; included in 
<figureCitation box="[976,1046,1496,1522]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1824,1850]" captionTargetBox="[186,1399,1156,1766]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[185,1400,1154,1767]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Distribution of the species of the Leiobunum rupestre species group. Red squares = L. rupestre Herbst, 1799; blue circles = L. gracile Thorell, 1876; green triangles = L. apenninicum (Martens, 1969); stippled line circumscribes area of L. subalpinum Komposch, 1998. Type localities are indicated by abbreviated taxon names (ape = apenninicum; gla = glabrum; gra = gracile; lae = laeve; nor = norvegicum; rup = rupestre; sub subalpinum; tis = tisciae). Arrows indicate a specified locality, if unprecisely given, the general area is indicated (rupestre = Saxony; gracile, laeve = Scania)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3840153" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3840153/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
